data.name: richTextBox1.Text
data.value:
This FAQ is extremely out of date, I don't know why I have not removed it yet. For better information check the foruns on http://www.pinkpetal.org
---------
---------
To get the game to load girls and random girls their respective *.girls(x) and *.rgirls(x) files must be placed under "Resources\Characters\" folder, while *.items(x) files go to "Resources\Data\" folder.
Excerpt from old manual:
To get the girls images to work, you need to create a folder in the Characters directory that goes by the same name as the girl. So if the girl is called Cammy White she should have a folder called Cammy White in the characters directory. The next step after creating the girl and her folder is to put images in there. There is a special way to name each picture. First it is important to know that there are several types of images for example sex images show scenes of normal sex while anal images are pictures containing anal sex. To make images show up correctly they need to be in .jpg format and they need to be named according to the type of image. Lastly they also need to be numbered counting from 1. So to give the character Cammy White 3 sex images you need 3 .jpg files named Sex1.jpg, Sex2.jpg and Sex3.jpg. The game will then use these images whenever a sex image needs to be shown. These are the names for images that are supported by the game:
Sex - For sex images Anal - for anal sex imagse BDSM - for bondage or submissive images Beast - for beastiality or sex with monsters Group - for sex with a group of people Profile - for normal images without sex Les - For lesbian themed images Preg - For pregnant images Death - For game over (or girl dies) images.
If the game cannot find an image it will use a default image from the default directory.
--------- New option for items was added (unused flag 3 from old manual). As far as I undrestood what it does is this:
It implements temporary effect to the items. First option (default) is normal item behaviour, the way items worked so far. Other two choices are new behaviours, "Affects all girls temporarily" and "Affects one girl temporarily". I think it's obvious what they do.
Only limit is this:
Temporary effects apply to traits, stats and skills, they don't apply to status' (it is logical, status' themselves are temporary, and have prior this change, only with different mechanics).
Traits that were added through this temporary mechanics will fade after 20 days, stats/skills that were added as temporary will fade by 1 point each day, until they're gone completely.

data.name: button_G_Divide_Real_Name.ToolTip
data.value: Click to divide the Girl's Real Name into First, Middle and Last This looks for the first and last names and anything between becomes the middle. If it only finds 1 name, that becomes the first. If it finds 2, they become first and last.

data.name: button_G_UnZero_Sex_Skills.ToolTip
data.value: If the girl you are editing does not have some of the sex skills set in it, this will check the existing sex skills and set the missing or zeroed sex skills to be similar to the existing sex skill numbers. It checks for 'round to 5 or 10' and 'number spreads'.

data.name: checkBox_RGTraitsReadOnly.ToolTip
data.value: I recommend simply deleting faulty entry and adding it back with correct value, but if you really, really, REALLY need it, you can unlock value field via this checkbox. Be SURE to enter only value between 0 and 100.

data.name: label26.ToolTip
data.value: Since these are random girls they get names from random name pool, this should be just name for girl type (template that corresponds to folder name with her pics), something like "Sporty girl", "Funny girl" and so on.

data.name: checkBox_DG3.ToolTip
data.value:
I recommend simply deleting entry and adding it again with correct value, but if you really, really, REALLY must, you can edit it manually.
Be very careful when manually editing value field to be sure to enter supported value.
Recognized values are "Add" and "Remove", everything else will be interpreted as "Remove".

data.name: checkBox_DG2.ToolTip
data.value:
I recommend simply deleting entry and adding it again with correct value, but if you really, really, REALLY must, you can edit it manually.
Be very careful when manually editing value field to be sure to enter supported value.
If you enter unsuported values (like "fasdsadfgdfvd" and like) you can expect that Whore Master will crash.

data.name: Label_Config_Control_Girls_Girls.ToolTip
data.value: Catacombs: Who gets What These settings will determine the ratio of Girls to Items to Beasts that they try to come back with. If the box is checked, these will control what they try to get when you send a Girl or Gang into the catacombs. The numbers entered here are normalized into fractions of 100% by the game. Negative numbers are not allowed and if all three are set to 0s, they wil be set to 33.33% each.

data.name: label178.ToolTip
data.value: Horoscope Type can either be "Tropical (Western)" or "Sideral (Hindu)". The only real difference is the dates that the Signs start and end. This is not really used in the game yet so either choice does not matter.

data.name: label155.ToolTip
data.value: This number is how long the girl remembers torture. If the number is above 0 then it is how many weeks some traits gained through torture last. If it is -1, then the torture is much harsher and the traits are permanent.

data.name: label_Load_Config.Text
data.value: The WME will try to find config.xml by itself. If it does not find it, you will have to find it manually. Starting in version .05t it is in the root game folder. In older versions, it was in \Resources\Data\ folder. In .06, the game will load the config.xml from the folder the .EXE is in and then from the folder above that. This means it loads it twice with the second one taking precidence. Leave anything out of the second that you want to have default to the game version folder.

data.name: richTextBox3.Text
data.value: You can set the location of certain folders to preserve your settings between game versions. They can be either Relative to the game's .EXE file or Absolute folder paths. For Relative path, start it with ".\" or use "..\" to go up a folder. Absolute paths start with "c:\" (or whatever drive you have it on). This section requires more knowledge of how folder paths work so it was moved to the extras tab.

data.name: richTextBox2.Text
data.value: This button will create a new random numbered folder in the same folder as the WME.exe It will then attempt to save every Girl, Rgirl and Item into their own files. If it comes across a file that already exists, it will create a numbered folder and place the new file in there. It will continue making numbered folders as long as there are multiple .girlsx, .rgirlsx or .itemsx with the same name.

data.name: checkBox_Add_Missing_Sex_Skills_On_Load.ToolTip
data.value: If you are loading an old girl file that does not have some of the sex skills set in it, this will check the existing sex skills and set the missing sex skills to be similar to the existing sex skill numbers. It checks for 'round to 5 or 10' and 'number spreads'. *** Currently only works for .girlsx files
